Hello all-

At the most recent GECCO, many people requested a webpage that would
have a description about research in Generative and Developmental
Systems. Specifically, people wanted a page that would point to papers
and sourcecode for GDS work, so that others could begin to play with
this technology themselves. The hope is that will generate more GDS
submissions, particularly at GECCO 2011.

I am please to announce that we have the seed of such a page here:

http://gds.wikispot.org/

Please check it out and add to it. Hopefully with the help of the
community it will turn into an even more valuable resource.


Best regards,
Jeff Clune

Postdoctoral Fellow
Hod Lipson's Computational Synthesis Laboratory
Cornell University
